<title>USA: Ampal-American factory shut after fire.</title>
<headline>Ampal-American factory shut after fire.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-06-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ampal-American Israel Corp said Friday the main factory of its majority-owned Paradise Mattresses (1992) Ltd unit was heavily damaged by fire Thursday night.</p>
<p>The company said the Bat Yam, Israel-based factory will be closed indefinitely.</p>
<p>The company said it is too soon to quantify losses from the fire. The company said it carries fire and business interruption insurance coverage for the facility.</p>
